      {
        "Id": "ed933e26f561453a8cd1ad965a39e4af",
        "Title": "So, this is super fun.\n\nAll of the various solids in the dwg related to the chambers get mashed into 1 solid. also, the surfaces of the titleblock do as well!\n\nSo, once we isolate the chamber surfaces from the topo surface using the layer key text, we are left with a flat list of surfaces to reconstruct.\n\nSo once we've tidied up our list structure, we run code that finds shared edges and groups surfaces accordingly,\n\nThen we attempt to union them back together.\n\nNow we have relatively few polysurfaces to clash against the line end points to see if the point should shift because it is the bottom rather than the top of the pipe.",
        "DescriptionText": null,
        "IsExpanded": true,
        "WidthAdjustment": 0.0,
        "HeightAdjustment": 0.0,
        "UserSetWidth": 0.0,
        "UserSetHeight": 0.0,
        "Nodes": [],
        "HasNestedGroups": false,
        "Left": 1945.682001240205,
        "Top": 1878.6988439870297,
        "Width": 0.0,
        "Height": 0.0,
        "FontSize": 36.0,
        "GroupStyleId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
        "InitialTop": 0.0,
        "InitialHeight": 0.0,
        "TextblockHeight": 0.0,
        "IsOptionalInPortsCollapsed": false,
        "IsUnconnectedOutPortsCollapsed": false,
        "HasToggledOptionalInPorts": false,
        "HasToggledUnconnectedOutPorts": false,
        "Background": "#FFC1D676"
      },
      {
        "Id": "49cec334bc0f4d1d81f6f501d376d410",
        "Title": "And another thing!  If the surfaces are on multiple layers, they appear to be merged onto 1 layer",
        "DescriptionText": null,
        "IsExpanded": true,
